  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ns/ontology/gist/isDirectPartOf">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty" />
    <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">DEFINITION: The relationship between a part and a whole where the part has independent existence and there are no other parts in between.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">NOTE: Because the part has independent existence, there is no cascading delete.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">NOTE: It is safest to use this property when semantic directness is inherent in the relationship, rather than simply expressing a chosen granularity. For example, a spark plug is a direct part of an engine block; there cannot be any intermediate parts. Otherwise, there is a risk of making an isDirectPartOf assertion and then later inserting an intermediate part; this will result in making an asserted triple false even though there was no change in the world. When in doubt, use the transitive version gist:isPartOf.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ontology/gistCore14.1.0" />
    <rdfs:label rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">is direct part of</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ns/ontology/gist/isPartOf" />
    <skos:definition rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">The relationship between a part and a whole where the part has independent existence and there are no other parts in between.</skos:definition>
    <skos:prefLabel rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">is direct part of</skos:prefLabel>
    <skos:scopeNote rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Because the part has independent existence, there is no cascading delete.</skos:scopeNote>
    <skos:scopeNote rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">It is safest to use this property when semantic directness is inherent in the relationship, rather than simply expressing a chosen granularity. For example, a spark plug is a direct part of an engine block; there cannot be any intermediate parts. Otherwise, there is a risk of making an isDirectPartOf assertion and then later inserting an intermediate part; this will result in making an asserted triple false even though there was no change in the world. When in doubt, use the transitive version gist:isPartOf.</skos:scopeNote>
  </rdf:Description>
